      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KEAYANG WASABI (12) was a beaten favourite in a higher-graded race last start but drew wide and had to work when covering ground so it may pay to be forgiving. Good effort to win at Terang prior. Proven here and is up to winning this with his A-game and even luck from the back row. GALAXY LASS (6) draws wider than in last week's narrow second at this venue but there was plenty of merit in that performance where she was held up before missing by a nose. Could atone if things go her way. CELESTIAL ZODIAC (4) had no clear run when beaten 3m last start. Came from this barrier to place the previous time he raced here. Major player. DELIGHTFUL CHARM (3) led and stuck on for a 1.3m second here last week and draws to be competitive again.",
